,"Decreased risk of infections"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ELong-term use of glucocorticoids can lead to \u003Cstrong\u003Eadrenal suppression\u003C/strong\u003E due to feedback inhibition of the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis. This can result in the body\u0027s reduced ability to produce endogenous glucocorticoids, especially during stress.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypotension\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucocorticoids typically cause hypertension, not hypotension\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIncreased muscle mass\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucocorticoids can cause muscle wasting rather than increasing muscle mass\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHypoglycaemia\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucocorticoids often lead to hyperglycaemia due to increased gluconeogenesis\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDecreased risk of infections\u003C/strong\u003E - Glucocorticoids suppress the immune system, increasing the risk of infections\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Glucocorticoids can cause adrenal suppression due to feedback inhibition of the hypothalamic-pituitary-adrenal axis.","Long-term glucocorticoid use can lead to osteoporosis, hyperglycaemia, and increased risk of infections.","Glucocorticoids can cause hypertension, not hypotension, as a side effect."],"references":["Waller, D. G., \u0026 Hitchings, A. W. (2021). Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book: Medical Pharmacology and Therapeutics E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Tashjian, A. H., \u0026 Armstrong, E. J. (2011). Principles of pharmacology: the pathophysiologic basis of drug therapy. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Queremel Milani DA, Davis DD. Pain Management Medications. 2023 Jul 3. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 32809527","Carter GT, Duong V, Ho S, Ngo KC, Greer CL, Weeks DL. Side effects of commonly prescribed analgesic medications. Phys Med Rehabil Clin N Am. 2014 May;25(2):457-70. doi: 10.1016/j.pmr.2014.01.007. PMID: 24787343","Rice JB, White AG, Scarpati LM, Wan G, Nelson WW. Long-term Systemic Corticosteroid Exposure: A Systematic Literature Review. Clin Ther. 2017 Nov;39(11):2216-2229. doi: 10.1016/j.clinthera.2017.09.011. Epub 2017 Oct 19. PMID: 29055500."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59283"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18204"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59283","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/59283"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-24T04:29:57+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-24T04:31:29+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10918"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"73808"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups